ent-CMHeadBeretEngineer-name = engineering beret
ent-CMHeadBeretEngineer-desc = A beret with the engineering insignia emblazoned on it. For engineers that are more inclined towards style than safety.
ent-CMHeadBeretCMP-name = UNMC Chief MP beret
ent-CMHeadBeretCMP-desc = A beret with the UNMC Military Police insignia emblazoned on it. It shines with the glow of corrupt authority and a smudge of doughnut.
ent-CMHeadBeretCO-name = CO's beret
ent-CMHeadBeretCOBlack-name = CO's beret
ent-CMHeadBeretCOBlack-desc = A black beret with the Major insignia emblazoned on it. Its sleek black color commands power and exudes class.
ent-CMHeadBeretCOWhite-name = CO's beret
ent-CMHeadBeretCOWhite-desc = A white beret with the Major insignia emblazoned on it. Its dazzling white color commands power and exudes class.
ent-CMHeadBeretCOLtCol-name = CO's lieutenant colonel beret
ent-CMHeadBeretCOLtCol-desc = A blue beret with the Lieutenant Colonel's insignia emblazoned on it. Its blue color symbolizes loyalty, confidence, and politics - the core components of a true Colonel.
ent-CMHeadBeretCOCol-name = CO's colonel beret
ent-CMHeadBeretCOCol-desc = A dark blue, custom-tailored beret signifying The Colonel. Definitely not an alias for a General.
ent-RMCHeadBeretGreen-name = UNMC beret
ent-RMCHeadBeretASO-name = ASO beret
ent-RMCHeadBeretASO-desc = A black beret worn by Auxiliary Support Officers.
ent-RMCHeadBeretPurple-name = purple beret
ent-RMCHeadBeretPurple-desc = A stylish, if purple, beret.
ent-CMHeadCapMP-name = MP cap
ent-CMHeadCapMP-desc = A ball-cap worn by the more casual of the Marines' Military Police.
ent-CMHeadCapWarden-name = warden cap
ent-CMHeadCapWarden-desc = Smells like donuts.
ent-CMHeadCapCargo-name = cargo cap
ent-CMHeadCapCargo-desc = It's a baseball hat in a tasteless yellow color.
