ent-CMHeadCapCOFormalWhite-name = CO's formal cap
ent-CMHeadCapDrill-name = drill hat
ent-CMHeadCapDrill-desc = From now on you will speak only when spoken to, and the first and last words out of your filthy sewers will be 'Sir.'
ent-CMHeadCapOfficer-name = UNMC officer cap
ent-CMHeadCapOfficer-desc = A hat usually worn by officers in the UNMC. While it provides no protection, some officers wear it in the field to make themselves more recognisable.
ent-RMCHeadCapASO-name = UNMC ASO cap
ent-RMCHeadCapASO-desc = A hat usually worn by ASOs in the UNMC. Provides no protection, but makes you look better when sorting papers.
ent-CMHeadCapPeakedFormal-name = marine peaked cap
ent-CMHeadCapPeakedFormal-desc = A peaked cap. Wearer may suffer the heavy weight of responsibility upon their head and shoulders.
ent-CMHeadCapPeakedService-name = marine service peaked cap
ent-CMHeadCapPeakedService-desc = A peaked cap. Wearer may suffer the heavy weight of responsibility upon their head and shoulders.
ent-RMCHeadCapPeakedASO-name = ASO peaked cap
ent-RMCHeadCapPeakedASO-desc = A peaked cap. Wearer may suffer the heavy weight of responsibility upon their head and shoulders.
ent-RMCHeadCapPeakedCMP-name = chief mp peaked cap
ent-RMCHeadCapPeakedCMP-desc = A peaked cap given to experienced CMP. Wearer may suffer the heavy weight of responsibility upon their head and shoulders.
ent-CMHeadCapCMO-name = chief medical officer's peaked cap
ent-CMHeadCapCMO-desc = A peaked cap given to high-ranking medical officers. Looks just a touch silly.
ent-CMHeadFlapCap-name = UNMC expedition cap
ent-CMHeadFlapCap-desc = It's a cap, with flaps. A patch stitched across the front reads "UNS ALMAYER".
ent-RMCHeadCapCorrespondent-name = combat correspondent cap
ent-RMCHeadCapCorrespondent-desc = A faithful cap for any terrain war correspondents may find themselves in.
ent-RMCHeadBlueSoftCap-name = blue cap
ent-RMCHeadBlueSoftCap-desc = It's a baseball hat in a tasteless blue color.
ent-RMCHeadYellowSoftCap-name = yellow cap
ent-RMCHeadYellowSoftCap-desc = It's a baseball hat in a tasteless yellow color.
ent-CMHeadCapSurgBlue-name = blue surgical cap
ent-CMHeadCapSurgBlue-desc = A cap surgeons wear during operations. Keeps their hair from tickling your internal organs.
ent-CMHeadCapSurgGreen-name = green surgical cap
ent-CMHeadCapSurgPurple-name = purple surgical cap
ent-CMHeadCapSurgOrange-name = orange surgical cap
ent-CMHeadDressBlues-name = marine dress blues cover
ent-CMHeadDressBlues-desc = The combination cover of the legendary Marine dress blues, virtually unchanged since the 19th century. The polished logo sits proudly on the white cloth.
ent-CMHeadDressBluesOfficer-name = marine dress blues officer cover
ent-CMHeadDressBluesOfficer-desc = The combination cover of the legendary Marine dress blues, virtually unchanged since the 19th century. Features a gold stripe and silvered logo, emblematic of an officer.
ent-RMCHeadBeretSquad-name = UNMC squad beret
ent-RMCHeadBeretSquad-desc = For those who want to show pride and have nothing to lose (in their head, at least).
ent-RMCHeadBeretSquadAlpha-name = UNMC squad beret
ent-RMCHeadBeretSquadAlpha-desc = Often found atop heads, slightly less found on those still attached.
ent-RMCHeadBeretSquadBravo-desc = It has quite a lot of debris on it, the person wearing this probably moves less than a wall.
ent-RMCHeadBeretSquadCharlie-desc = Still has some morning toast crumbs on it.
ent-RMCHeadBeretSquadDelta-desc = Hard to consider protection, but these types of people don't seek protection.
ent-RMCHeadBeretSquadEcho-desc = Tightly Woven, as it should be.
ent-RMCHeadBeretSquadFoxtrot-desc = Looks and feels starched, cold to the touch.
ent-RMCHeadBeretSquadIntel-desc = Looks more intellegent than the person wearing it.
ent-RMCProvostCommandBeret-name = UNMC provost command beret
ent-RMCProvostCommandBeret-desc = A beret with the UNMC Military Police insignia emblazoned on it.
ent-RMCHeadBeanie-name = beanie
ent-RMCHeadBeanie-desc = A standard military beanie, often worn by non-combat military personnel and support crews, though it is not uncommon to see combat personnel who no longer care about self-preservation wearing one of these as well. Popular due to being comfortable and snug.
ent-RMCHeadBeanieTan-name = tan beanie
ent-RMCHeadBeanieGray-name = gray beanie
ent-RMCHeadBeanieGreen-name = green beanie
ent-RMCHeadBeanieCargo-name = cargo beanie
ent-RMCHeadBeanieTSE-name = royal marine beanie
ent-RMCHeadBeanieTSE-desc = A standard military beanie.
ent-RMCHeadRadiationHood-name = radiation hood
ent-RMCHeadRadiationHood-desc = A hood with radiation protective properties. Label: Made with lead, do not eat insulation
ent-RMCHeadWeYaPilotCap-name = Weston-Yamada Pilot cap
ent-RMCHeadWeYaPilotCap-desc = A dark peaked cap enscribed with the Weston-Yamada 'Wings' logo. A formal cap for qualified civillian Pilots, akin to old Earth formal Pilots-wear.
ent-RMCHeadDurag-name = durag
ent-RMCHeadDurag-desc = An improvised head wrap made out of a standard issue neckerchief. Great for keeping the sweat out of your eyes and protecting your hair.
ent-RMCHeadDuragBlack-desc = An improvised head wrap made out of a black neckerchief. Great for keeping the sweat out of your eyes and protecting your hair.
ent-RMCHeadCapGrey-name = grey cap
ent-RMCHeadCapGrey-desc = It's a baseball hat in a tasteful grey color.
ent-RMCHeadCapFerret-name = ferret heavy industries trucker hat
ent-RMCHeadCapFerret-desc = It's a trucker hat. They're becoming collector items since Ferret went under in 2080.
ent-RMCHeadCapTruckerRed-name = red trucker hat
